# MyOrbit Calendar Application - Key Features & Architecture

## Current State (UPDATED January 2025)
✅ **PRODUCTION READY** - The application is feature-complete with real-time cross-device sync, external calendar integration (Google + Apple), and all core calendar/contact features fully implemented and tested.

## Major Features Complete ✅

### Real-Time Cross-Device Sync (NEW)
- **Supabase Realtime** WebSocket subscriptions for instant sync
- **Conflict Resolution** with Last-Write-Wins strategy (timestamp-based)
- **Offline Sync Queue** with automatic retry and exponential backoff
- **Works on all platforms** (iOS, Android, Web, macOS, Windows)
- Implementation: `RealtimeSyncService`, `ConflictResolutionService`, `SyncQueueService`

### External Calendar Integration (NEW)
- **Google Calendar Import:** Full OAuth integration, one-way event import
  - Services: `GoogleCalendarSyncService`, `GoogleCalendarProvider`
  - Packages: `googleapis`, `google_sign_in`, OAuth authentication
  - Maps Google Calendar visibility to MyOrbit privacy levels
- **Apple Calendar Import:** iOS/macOS EventKit integration
  - Services: `AppleCalendarSyncService`, `AppleCalendarProvider`
  - Native code: `ios/Runner/AppDelegate.swift`, `macos/Runner/AppDelegate.swift`
  - Platform channel: `com.myorbit/apple_calendar`
  - Permissions: `NSCalendarsUsageDescription`, `NSCalendarsFullAccessUsageDescription`
  - Entitlement: `com.apple.security.personal-information.calendars`

### Availability Signals
- Sophisticated availability sharing system where users can broadcast their availability during specific time windows
- Four signal types: Available, Busy, Flexible, Unavailable
- Users explicitly select which contacts can see each signal (independent of general permissions)
- Smart buffer system (0-120 minutes) around events to protect signal availability
- Automatic conflict detection and resolution between events and signals
- Signal preferences per contact (notifications, auto-accept settings)

### Privacy Controls
- 3-tier contact permissions: Private, Semi-Visible, Visible
- 3-tier event privacy levels: Normal, Exclusive, Super Exclusive
- Sophisticated override hierarchy:
  1. Explicit event invitation → always grants full details
  2. Event privacy level → overrides partner permissions
  3. Partner permission level → default visibility
- Signal sharing operates independently with explicit contact selection

### Event Management
- Full event creation with title, description, calendar selection, time, and recurrence
- Smart recurrence patterns: One-off, Weekly, Biweekly, Monthly with AI suggestions
- Conflict detection between events and availability signals
- Multi-calendar support with visibility toggling
- Buffer management around events

### Calendar Views & Navigation
- Month, Week, and Day calendar views with sophisticated event rendering
- Bottom navigation with Dashboard, Calendar, Activity, and People tabs
- Advanced timezone handling with user-configurable settings
- Multi-calendar support with color coding and visibility controls

### Technical Architecture
- Full Riverpod state management implementation
- GoRouter navigation with deep linking
- Supabase backend integration with RLS (Row Level Security)
- Offline-first architecture with local storage fallback
- Comprehensive error handling with Result type system
- Accessibility-first design with semantic widgets
- Timezone conversion system

### Backend Integration
- Supabase authentication (Google, Apple, email/password)
- Full CRUD operations for events, contacts, and signals
- Row Level Security policies for data isolation
- Local storage fallback when backend unavailable
- Comprehensive API service layer

### Settings & User Preferences
- Dark/Light theme support
- Timezone configuration
- Notification controls (granular per-feature)
- Default privacy settings
- Signal notification channels and buffer times
- Calendar sync preferences

## Database Schema
- Profiles table with user information and timezone preferences
- Contacts table with permission levels and status tracking
- Events table with privacy levels, recurrence, and calendar assignment
- Availability signals table with start/end times and types
- Signal shares table for tracking who can see which signals
- Calendars table for multi-calendar support
- Calendar visibility table for visibility preferences
- Recurrence rules table for smart event patterns
- Event invites table for invitation tracking

