## Dependency Management Rule
- When upgrading packages, always confirm that SDK-provided libraries (e.g., `flutter_test`) and tightly pinned dependencies (such as `encrypt`, `mockito`, `test`) accept the new versions before changing constraints. Run `flutter pub outdated` first, adjust versions only within compatible ranges, and document any pins that block upgrades so future updates can be revisited safely.

